
// This Hyperlambda code snippet uses the [set-value] slot to update the value of a node by replacing a placeholder string within a template. The [strings.replace] slot is used to find and replace occurrences of "{{name}}" with "Sarah" in the node referenced by [@.template].
set-value:x:-
   strings.replace:x:@.template
      .:{{name}}
      .:Sarah
